  "body": "## Summary\r\nIf used method hardhat.upgrades.deployProxy(), created directory '.openzeppelin' in root path in project.\r\nAlso, generated json file in directory. example below,\r\n\r\nunknown-1337.json (network name + chain id + .json)\r\n\r\nIf generate new network after network initialization (reset network and 'npx hardhat clean') , hardhat is set up with the '.openzeppelin' directory you created in the old network. furthermore if you set the same chain id as the previous network, it make problem when request method upgrades.deployProxy() on newly network.\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\n// validateStoredDeployment()\r\n.\r\n.\r\n. \r\nconst tx = await getTransactionByHash(provider, txHash);\r\nif (tx !== null) {\r\n  debug('resuming previous deployment', txHash);\r\n  if (merge) {\r\n       waitAndValidateDeployment(provider, stored, type, opts);\r\n    }\r\n} else {\r\n      // ****** error ****** \r\n      throw new InvalidDeployment(stored);\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe txHash in .openzeppelin/network-chainid.json is not exist in newly network because it created previous network.\r\n\r\n## Suggest\r\nAdd job in hardhat cli task 'clean'.\r\n\r\nAs-is : Remove directory 'artifacts', emptyDir 'cache'.\r\nSuggest : Remove directory 'artifacts', emptyDir 'cache', **'.openzeppelin'**.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
